         <notesStmt>
            <note>
								Yitsḥaḳ ben Yudah of Tulusa (Toulouse): inscribed with his name on the frontispiece and in the colophon, Solsona , Kislew 5145 [1384] (folios 2v, 427r). 
								Laurentius D'Arvieux (b. 1635, d. 1702), French traveller and diplomat, consul for France and Holland at Aleppo: Latin title page added by him (folio 1r); purchased in 1683. Latin account on the history of the manuscript, 16th century (folio 1v).  
								Benjamin Kennicott (b. 1718, d. 1783), English biblical scholar: his translation of the Latin account on folio 1v, 1768 (a paper sheet affixed on folio [i verso]). 
								King George III (b. 1738, d. 1820): his stamp on upper and lower covers. </note>
            <note type="relatedResource">
								Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.
							</note>
